<h2 id="org2796dda">Git Config</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2796dda">
<p>
You can set the settings for a git repo with the <code>git config</code> command.
</p>

<p>
These settings are written to a file <code>.gitconfig</code> if <code>git config --local</code> is used.
</p>

<p>
You can list settings with <code>git config --list</code>.
</p>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgaa55c74" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgaa55c74">Common Settings</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgaa55c74">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org823704f" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org823704f">User</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org823704f">
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[<span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">user</span>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">email</span> = example@email.com
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">name</span> = John Doe
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5911fc3" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org5911fc3">Gui</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org5911fc3">
<p>
Heres how you can set the editor to <a href="../20220428224740-emacs.html#ID-95b6342a-ca5b-4f59-9f08-6cbd3aedf7a2">emacs</a>
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[<span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">gui</span>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">editor</span> = emacs
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org2072ac4" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org2072ac4">init</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org2072ac4">
<p>
If you need to set the default branch heres how you can do so.
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-conf">[<span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">init</span>]
  <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">defaultBranch</span> = dev
</pre>
</div>
</div>
